From: OpenVINO ROCm Plugin <noreply@openvino.org>
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] Fix LDS bank conflicts for f16 with kpack>1

For f16 (2 bytes/elem) with kpack>1, the original stride=1 only shifts
2 bytes between adjacent lanes, leaving them in the same 4-byte LDS bank.
Use bankWidth/elemBytes (=2 for f16) as stride to ensure adjacent lanes
hit different banks.

Measured impact: ~3-5% improvement on gfx1100 WMMA conv kernels with
kpack>1 (e.g. 3x3 stride=1 fp16 shapes).
---
diff --git a/mlir/lib/Dialect/Rock/utility/loweringUtils.cpp b/mlir/lib/Dialect/Rock/utility/loweringUtils.cpp
index 64b3e8973404..44e2df8a2c76 100644
--- a/mlir/lib/Dialect/Rock/utility/loweringUtils.cpp
+++ b/mlir/lib/Dialect/Rock/utility/loweringUtils.cpp
@@ -1148,7 +1148,12 @@ FailureOr<Value> mlir::rock::wrapLDSBufferForStore(
   // buffer has the benefit of minimizing bank conflicts when we are transposing
   // the matrix from global to LDS. I.e., instead of storing different items in
   // position (0,0), (1,0), (2,0), ... we store it in (0,0), (1,1), (2, 2), ...
-  int64_t stride = (kpack == 1 ? dPerThread : 1);
+  // Stride must cover at least one LDS bank (4 bytes) to avoid conflicts.
+  // For f16 (2 bytes/elem) with kpack>1, stride=1 only shifts 2 bytes,
+  // leaving adjacent lanes in the same bank. Use bankWidth/elemBytes instead.
+  int64_t elemBytes = dataType.getIntOrFloatBitWidth() / 8;
+  int64_t bankWidthElems = std::max(int64_t(1), int64_t(4) / elemBytes);
+  int64_t stride = (kpack == 1 ? dPerThread : bankWidthElems);
   TopDownTMBuilder reshapeBuf = rotateIf(
       rotateDWithK, mergeKpack, mergeKpackAttr, stride, dName, d, 1, "k_outer",
       kOuter, {"k_outer"}, {"kpack_idx", "kpack_vec"}, transformAttrs);
